Windows Boot Process:
BIOS/EFI > MBR > Vol Boot Sector > Bootmgr.exe > Winload.exe > Ntoskrnl.exe > Smss.exe > Crss.exe > Wininit.exe > Services.exe > svchost.exe
wininit.exe > lsass.exe
crss.exe > winlogin.exe > userinit.exe > userinit.exe > explorer.exe
BIOS UEFI:
ROM - Read only mem
EPROM - Erasable Programmable Read only memory
EEPROM - Electronically Erasable Programmable read only memory
Flash Mem
UEFI vs BIOS - Faster, loaded into flash mem/EEPROM, secured boot, drive support
MBR (Master Boot Record) - Disk Partitions, starts first stage of OS called Boot Loader and starts OS
UEFI - MBR reads EFI Partition that contains bootmgfw.efi (WinBtmgr)
**winload.exe = BIOS, winload.efi = UEFI
UEFI systems - bootmgfw.efi reads BCD (boot config data) to load winload.efi
BIOS systems - bootmgr reads file \Boot\BCD winload.exe to load basic drivers and the kernel
winresume.exe reads saved data from hiberfil.sys
!! For the user subsystems, just look at the FG man
Session 0 - security and hi priv processes to isolate from a user's processes
Session 1 - For the user to interact with, contains STANDARD user sessions
