System Calls:
- Interaction b/w process/kernel | prograam request service from kernel
fork - duplicates calling process into a child | calling process is parent
exec - process call exec, kernel start prog and replaces curr proc
Signals - software interrupts
        - Stop 19 | End 15 | Kill 9
Fore/Background Processes:
Foreground Process - req user interaction | prog/comm default to foreground
background - ran indendent of the user
orphan - parent process has finished and adopted by sbin/init w/ ppid 1
zombie - completed execution but not kill by parent process | takes up pids | killed only thru ppid
daemon - runs as bg ps | always orphans (not vice versa) | manage/monitor service | should persist thru entire sys ops | init parent | service | naming convention adds 'd' to service names 
Job Control - stop/suspend/continue/resume exe of proc
